Non sponsored, this routine works perfectly for fading mild acne marks or PIH on my dry, acne-prone skin "over the time" don't expect overnight magic 🤨

When my skin is doing well, I like to include a peptide serum after my toner. But when I'm targeting specific concerns, I skip it too many layers can actually reduce the efficacy of treatment serums.

Here’s what I currently use (product links are in my bio, or feel free to drop a comment):

1. Gentle Cleanser
COSRX Advanced Snail Mucin Gel Cleanser – This was PR, and I personally love it. I don’t have a snail mucin allergy, and it leaves my skin soft, plump, and clean without drying.

Alternatives: If you’re allergic to snail mucin, try the @cosrx_india_official Low pH Good Morning Gel Cleanser or Dot & Key Barrier Repair Cleanser (great budget pick).

2. Toner
Tony Moly Wonder Ceramide Mochi Toner – My holy grail! Lightweight, yet moisturizing perfect for prepping dry skin before applying serums.

3. Treatment Serum
@worldofasaya Kojic Acid + Alpha Arbutin Serum – This absorbs quickly, is non-comedogenic, and has given me visible results.
Alternate Option: Juicy Chemistry Alpha Arbutin + D-Gallic Acid – This was PR, and I’m currently alternating between this and Asaya’s to test its long-term effects.

4. Moisturizer
Maxrich Moisturizer  Recommended by my dermatologist. It gives long-lasting hydration and that dewy, glass-skin look.

Other options: Cetaphil or Beauty of Joseon Dynasty Cream are also great picks for hydration.

5. Sunscreen
I rotate sunscreens a lot, but two of my absolute favorites are:

Beauty of Joseon Relief Sun: Rice + Probiotics
Isntree Hyaluronic Acid Watery Sun Gel
Budget pick: The Derma Co Hyaluronic Acid Sunscreen light, hydrating, and affordable

Non sponsored! First off, at-home peeling solutions are not meant for daily use they’re best used just once a week as part of your exfoliation routine. And please, be careful if you're planning to try one! On peel days, skip all other active ingredients. Just cleanse your face, apply the peel, rinse it off as directed, and follow up with a rich, nourishing moisturizer at night. And don’t forget sunscreen the next day it's a must!

I've tested a ton of exfoliating peels some became my holy grail, while others were complete disasters. There were mornings I woke up glowing, and others when I dealt with redness and irritation. So, choose your peeling solution wisely. Don’t just experiment randomly always check the strength. Start with a low-strength peel to see how your skin reacts, and only move to higher strengths if you're comfortable. Or honestly, you might find the gentler ones work perfectly for you!

Non sponsored, these are my top favorites and I'd repurchase them in a heartbeat:

– @tirtir_global Hydro Boost Cleansing Balm
Suits all skin types. I love everything about it the ingredients, how effectively it removes makeup except the packaging. I wish it came with a spatula, because scooping it out with my fingers feels unhygienic.

– @laneige_in Vitamin C Sunscreen
I usually hate Vitamin C, but this sunscreen has the best form of it. It brightens the skin while protecting against UV rays an absolute win!

– @fclskincare AHA Lightening Serum
I’ve mentioned this in almost every video it’s my holy grail for treating pigmentation. But be careful: it’s very strong, so definitely do a patch test before using.

– @belifindia Aqua Jelly Cleanser
It’s pricey for a facewash, but I’d repurchase it without a second thought. It makes my dry skin feel so soft and plump, without stripping away moisture.

– TIRTIR Milk Toner
My dry skin drinks this up! It gives the most beautiful glowy, dewy finish. I really hope they never discontinue it.

– The Derma Co x Dr. V Retinol
When I wanted to start using retinol but needed something hydrating for my dry skin, this was exactly what I needed. It’s gentle yet effective.

– Solved Calm Balm Cleansing Balm
The best budget-friendly cleansing balm I’ve found with amazing packaging and clean ingredients. It has a mild fragrance, but it didn’t irritate my skin at all.

– Suganda Cleansing Oil
Outperforms any expensive oil I’ve tried! It’s non-comedogenic, removes makeup in seconds, and is super budget-friendly 

– Maxrich Yu Moisturizer
Recommended by my dermatologist when my skin barrier was severely damaged. It gives a gorgeous dewy finish and keeps my skin moisturized for hours.
